The '''1991 [[Tel Aviv Open|Riklis Classic]]''' was a [[tennis]] tournament played on [[hard court]]s that was part of the [[ATP World Series|World Series]] of the [[1991 ATP Tour]]. It was played at the [[Israel Tennis Centers]] at [[Ramat HaSharon]] near [[Tel Aviv]] in [[Israel]] from October 7 through October 14, 1991.

==Champions==
===Men's Singles===
{{main|1991 Riklis Classic – Singles}}
{{flagicon|MEX}} '''[[Leonardo Lavalle]]''' defeated {{flagicon|RSA|1928}} [[Christo van Rensburg]] 6&ndash;2, 3&ndash;6, 6&ndash;3
* It was Lavalle's only title of the year and the 4th of his career.

===Men's Doubles===
{{main|1991 Riklis Classic – Doubles}}
{{flagicon|CSK}} '''[[David Rikl]]''' / {{flagicon|NED}} '''[[Michiel Schapers]]''' defeated {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Javier Frana]] / {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Leonardo Lavalle]] 6&ndash;2, 6&ndash;7, 6&ndash;3
* It was Rikl's only title of the year and the 1st of his career. It was Schapers' only title of the year and the 3rd of his career.

