'''Belt-sander racing''' is the practice of racing [[belt sander]]s competitively. Belt sanders were one of the first power tools used in the growing field of power tool [[drag racing]]{{cn|date=September 2013}} wherein a pair of stock or modified belt sanders are placed in parallel wooden channels and fitted with long [[extension cord]]s.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2000/02/03/technology/screen-grab-a-sport-for-purists-belt-sander-races.html | title=A Sport for Purists: Belt-Sander Races | publisher=New York Times | date=February 3, 2000 | accessdate=June 24, 2012 | author=Pollak, Michael}}</ref> Each heat begins when a common switch or individual switches triggered by the racers energizes them, causing the sanders to race towards the end of the track spitting wood dust along the way.  Both stock sanders  and modified sanders race down a {{convert|75|foot}} long track. Sanders of all shapes and sizes can go very fast, or very slow depending on the power of the motor.  The fastest time on a 75-foot track was 2.2103 seconds recorded by Dudley Harper's Sudden Death Racer of San Marcos, Texas.  Sudden Death raced on that date at the Legends Raceway in Rockport, Texas.  The peak velocity of that belt sander at the finish line was in the range of {{convert|50|–|60|mph}}.<ref>{{Cite web|title = SoTex Belt Sander Racing Association|url = https://www.facebook.com/SoTexBeltSanderRacingAssociation|website = www.facebook.com|accessdate = 2015-09-21}}</ref>

== Fundraising ==
For more than two decades, Bertie's Inn in Reading, Pennsylvania has held a fundraiser called Bertie's Inn Belt Sander Race.  Riders sit on and race hand-held belt sanders on a 40-foot-long plywood track.  All team entry fees ($50), food sales and T-shirts sales are donated to the [[National Multiple Sclerosis Society]].  Their most recent race was July 16, 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bertiesinn.com/beltsanderrace.html|title=Bertie's Belt Sander Race|last=Thomas|first=William P.|website=www.bertiesinn.com|access-date=2018-09-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nationalmssociety.org/chapters/pae/fundraising-events/community-fundraisers/berties-belt-sander-race/index.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-03-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925124928/http://www.nationalmssociety.org/chapters/pae/fundraising-events/community-fundraisers/berties-belt-sander-race/index.aspx |archivedate=2013-09-25 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www2.readingeagle.com/article.aspx?id=395378|title=Belt-sander race to benefit Multiple Sclerosis Society|website=Reading Eagle|access-date=2018-09-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www2.readingeagle.com/article.aspx?id=493027|title=Riding sanders a blast at charity event|website=Reading Eagle|access-date=2018-09-15}}</ref>

