'''FPS''' (full name: '''Forssan Palloseura''') is a [[Finland|Finnish]] [[ice hockey]] team based in [[Forssa Ice Hall]] (capacity 3000), [[Forssa]], established in [[1931 in sports|1931]]. Forssan Palloseura has two lower level teams: FoPS which plays in lower divisions and FoPS Flames which plays in the [[2. Divisioona]] league.

FoPS Flames gained some negative news after former [[SM-liiga]] and Forssan Palloseura [[defenceman]] [[Timo Willman]] assaulted an opposing player during a [[3. Divisioona|3rd Division]] game in 2007.{{Citation needed|date=September 2010}}

Most famous FPS figures are former NHL-coach [[Alpo Suhonen]] and player [[Mika Helkearo]] who are nicknamed the "[[Mestis|Divarin]] [[Wayne Gretzky|Gretzky]]" (Gretzky of the [[Mestis|1st Division]]) from his virtually unbreakable [[Mestis]] records in games, assists and points.

