}}
'''José Luis Rocha''' represented México in the [[Diving at the 1984 Summer Olympics - Men's 10 metre platform|1984 Olympic Games]] in Diving. Rocha was born in [[México City]].  He attended [[Auburn University]]<ref>[http://auburntigers.cstv.com/sports/c-swim/aub-c-swim-body.html "Auburn University"]</ref> where he was a member of the Swimming and Diving Teams from 1986 to 1989. Rocha was named "an All-American"<ref>[http://auburntigers.cstv.com/sports/c-swim/spec-rel/aub-m-swim-all-am.html "an All-American"]</ref> each of his years at Auburn University, and won the 1987 [[National Collegiate Athletic Association]] (NCAA) National Championship on the 1-meter event.

He graduated from Auburn in 1989 with a bachelor's degree in Criminal Justice and moved to South Florida where he married U.S. Olympic Diver and Double Olympic Silver Medalist, [[Michele Mitchell (diver)|Michele Mitchell]],<ref>[http://www.ishof.org/Honorees/95/95mmitchell.html Michele Mitchell] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081203233817/http://www.ishof.org/Honorees/95/95mmitchell.html |date=2008-12-03 }}</ref> and became a US Citizen. Rocha worked as a police officer with the Delray Beach Police Department<ref>[http://www.mydelraybeach.com/Delray/Departments/Police/default.htm "Delray Beach Police Department"]</ref> in [[Palm Beach County]], and later moved with his family to [[Tucson]], Arizona<ref>[http://tpdinternet.tucsonaz.gov/ "Tucson, Arizona,"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081103234656/http://tpdinternet.tucsonaz.gov/ |date=2008-11-03 }}</ref> where he also served as a police officer. Michele Mitchell and Jose Luis Rocha were divorced in 2006 and Rocha moved to Austin, Texas where he worked as a [[Private Investigator]]. He joined the [[United States Army]]<ref>[http://www.army.mil/ "United States Army"]</ref> in 2007, and has deployed twice in support of Operation Iraqi Freedom and Operation New Dawn.

