''This article is about the magazine. For the article about the Tv show, [[O Jogo (2003 Brazilian TV series)|Click here.]]'' {{Infobox Newspaper |name = O Jogo |image = O Jogo.gif |image_size = 150px |caption = Front page of ''O Jogo'' from 22 May 2008 |type = Daily Sports [[newspaper]] |format = [[Tabloid format|Tabloid]] |owners = [[Global Media Group]] |foundation = {{start date and age|df=yes|1985|2|22}} |language = [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] |editor = |website = [https://www.ojogo.pt/ ''O Jogo''] |circulation = 28,900 (2010) |headquarters = [[Porto]] }} '''''O Jogo''''' ([[English language|English]]: ''The Game'') is a [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] daily [[sport]] [[newspaper]] published in [[Porto]], Portugal.
==History and profile== ''O Jogo'' was first published on 22 February 1985 by the [[Jornal de Notícias]] company in [[Porto]], and it is seen as appealing mainly to supporters of [[FC Porto]],<ref name=kumar>{{cite book|author=Prasidh Kumar Mishra|title=Sports Journalism|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Jcfml8Fqy1wC&pg=PT167|date=10 October 2010|publisher=Pinnacle Technology|isbn=978-1-61820-463-9|page=167}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.novidadestv.com/2012/09/04/benfica-contra-oliveira-pt-e-zon/|title=Benfica contra Oliveira, PT e Zon |trans-title=Benfica against [Joaquim] Oliveira, PT (Portugal Telecom) and ZON|language=Portuguese|date=4 September 2012|work=Correio da Manhã|accessdate=12 January 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130304055609/http://www.novidadestv.com/2012/09/04/benfica-contra-oliveira-pt-e-zon|archivedate=4 March 2013 }}</ref> being publicly criticized by [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/ArticleId/33868/language/pt-PT/Comunicado-O-Jogo-e-a-falta-de-vergonha.aspx|title=Comunicado: O Jogo e a falta de vergonha|trans-title=Press release: O Jogo and the lack of shame|date=13 January 2014|language=Portuguese|work=S.L. Benfica|accessdate=12 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/ArticleId/40507/language/pt-PT/Seis-milhoes-de-adeptos.aspx|title=Comunicado |language=Portuguese|trans-title=Announcement|date=4 February 2015|work=[[S.L. Benfica]]|accessdate=5 February 2015}}</ref> suppressing the gap of the two other national sports newspapers, ''[[A Bola]]'' and ''[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]''. ''O Jogo'' has also a [[Lisbon]] edition.
''O Jogo'' is published in [[tabloid format]].<ref>{{cite web|title=World Press Trends|url=http://www.wan-press.org/ecrire/upload/wpt2004.pdf|work=World Association of Newspapers|accessdate=15 February 2015|location=Paris|date=2004}}</ref> The paper was sold in 1995 to [[Lusomundo]] Media subsidiary Jornalinveste,<ref name=kumar/> which was later absorbed into Controlinveste in 2005 after Lusomundo Media merged with Olivedesportos, before renaming itself as [[Global Media Group]] in 2015.
==Circulation== The circulation of ''O Jogo'' was 34,837 copies in 2002, 40,677 copies in 2003 and 49,809 copies in 2004.<ref name=paulo>{{cite web|author=Paulo Faustino|title=Media Concentration, Market Dynamics and Pluralism of Information: the Portuguese case|url=http://paperroom.ipsa.org/papers/paper_16597.pdf|work=International Political Science Association|accessdate=4 December 2014}}</ref> The circulation of the paper was 44,878 copies in 2005, 41,473 copies in 2006 and 35,976 copies in 2007.<ref name=paulo/> Its 2010 circulation was 28,900 copies.<ref name=circulation>[http://www.ligateamedia.pt/LigateaMedia/Artigos/Imprensa/ArticleItem.aspx?tabid=2414&code=pt&ItemId=315 Imprensa: Circulation Portugal 2010] Retrieved 22 August 2011 (pt)</ref>
