'''Thomas Lennard, 1st Earl of Sussex, 15th Baron Dacre''', (13 May 1654 – 30 October 1715) was an [[England|English]] [[Peerage|peer]]. He became [[Earl of Sussex]] in 1674 when he married [[Anne Lennard, Countess of Sussex|Lady Anne Fitzroy, illegitimate daughter of Charles II and Lady Anne Palmer]]. The [[Baron Dacre]] title became abeyant in 1715 following his death.<ref>[http://www.thepeerage.com/p433.htm thepeerage.com]</ref>

==Cricket==
Lennard was a supporter of [[cricket]] which developed into a [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Cricket#MAJOR|major sport]] during his lifetime.  His 1677 accounts include an item which refers to £3 being paid to him when he went to a cricket match being played at "[[Lower Dicker|ye Dicker]]" (''sic''), which was then a common in the vicinity of [[Hailsham]] in [[East Sussex]].<ref>McCann, p. xl.</ref>

